This paper deals with the comparison of citation networks of journals in two different databases, namely Scopus and Web of Science. The paper involves network analysis and mapping, which are techniques commonly used in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SD), and cybernetics (cs.CY). However, given the focus on journal citation relations, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
